1. Copy .env.template to .env 
2. Fill out .env variables
3. Build docker image with 'docker build -t kettlewright .'
4. Run 'docker run -it --user $(id -u):$(id -g) --env-file .env -v $(pwd)/instance:/app/instance kettlewright /bin/sh'
5. Run 'flask db upgrade' from the shell, then 'exit'
6. Lunch the application with 'docker run --user $(id -u):$(id -g) -v $(pwd)/instance:/app/instance --env-file .env -p 8000:8000 kettlewright'
7. Access Kettlewright at http://127.0.0.1:8000
from the src folder

Note:
For MacOS, you will need to add quotes around the commands in steps 4 and 6, and you will not need to run either command as the current user.

